commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan win by 6 wickets and they now lead the 2-match series 1-0!
198 was a modest target but it's always a tricky affair chasing small targets, especially in these kind of wickets but the Pakistan batsmen made it look easy.

The openers started off well adding 42 runs for the first wicket and that eased the pressure and put Pakistan right on top, Younis Khan came up with a gem of an innings, that took the game away from India. There was a bit of a wobble towards the end when Inzi got out but Akmal joined in and gave good support to Khan and they finished it off in style.
So Pakistan starts off with a comprehensive win which gives them an unassailable lead, Younis Khan has been awarded the man of the match award for his match-winning innings.
For the latest bulletin on today's play, features and other stories please visit www.cricinfo.com
That's all we have for you today, be sure to join us tomorrow at 11:30 GMT for the second and final match of the series, until then it's good bye from all of us here.
